# Interprocess Communication (IPC)

- Unnamed Pipes: only in one direction (half-duplex)
    ls -l | more
- Named Pipe or First Input, First Output (FIFO)
    mkfifo mypipe
    echo "read this" > mypipe  # it hold until read
    cat  mypipe   # (in another terminal) read and release echo
- Message Queues
- Shared memory
- Semaphores: when a process "allocates" (accesses) it waits (blocks) the other process to accesse it until process a "release"
  - binary semaphores: holds o or 1, locked or unlocked .... 
  - counting semaphores: allow arbitrary resource counters
- Signals


ipc # show Message Queues, Shared memory and Semaphores
